text.tspan: Long-run perspective on female labor force participation rates
Proportion of the female population ages 15 and over that is economically active.
Source: Our World In Data based on OECD (2017) and Long (1958)
Note: For some observations prior 1960, the participation rate is taken with respect to the female population 14 and over. See sources for details.
